        <caption>
          <p>Output of miRCat2 for a predicted sequence corresponding to hsa-mir-2110 (chromosome 10), depicting (<bold>A</bold>) precursor presence plots, (<bold>B</bold>) precursor secondary structure and (<bold>C</bold>) alignment of incident reads. <bold>(A)</bold> On the <italic>x</italic>-axis we represent each position along the miRNA hairpin; on the <italic>y</italic>-axis we represent the point abundance calculated as the algebraic sum of the abundances of incident reads. <bold>(B)</bold> Precursor secondary structure, color-coded for each nucleotide type (A—green, C—orange, G—red, T—black). <bold>(C)</bold> Alignment of incident reads on the precursor; the numbers of the right represent the raw read abundance. The last line presents the secondary structure in dot-bracket notation, together with its MFE</p>
